<% content_for :page_title, "Privacy Policy | Inkcreate" %>
<% content_for :page_description, "Inkcreate privacy policy covering account data, notebook content, uploaded photos, OCR processing, and Google Drive exports." %>

<div class="page-shell">
  <%= render "legal/topbar" %>

  <main class="legal-shell">
    <aside class="legal-sidebar">
      <section class="section-card legal-summary">
        <div class="eyebrow">Legal</div>
        <h1 class="legal-page-title">Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="legal-lead">
          This Privacy Policy explains how Inkcreate collects, uses, stores, and shares
          information when you use the website, workspace, OCR features, and Google Drive integration.
        </p>

        <dl class="legal-meta">
          <div>
            <dt>Effective date</dt>
            <dd><%= legal_effective_date %></dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt>Applies to</dt>
            <dd>Web app, mobile browser use, uploads, OCR, and Drive exports</dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt>Key categories</dt>
            <dd>Account data, notebook content, photos, usage data, and integration settings</dd>
          </div>
        </dl>
      </section>

      <nav class="section-card legal-nav" aria-label="Privacy policy sections">
        <a href="#scope">Scope</a>
        <a href="#information-we-collect">Information we collect</a>
        <a href="#how-we-use-information">How we use information</a>
        <a href="#ocr-storage-drive">OCR, storage, and Drive</a>
        <a href="#sharing">Sharing and disclosures</a>
        <a href="#retention">Retention and deletion</a>
        <a href="#security">Security</a>
        <a href="#choices">Your choices</a>
        <a href="#changes">Changes to this policy</a>
      </nav>
    </aside>

    <article class="section-card legal-article">
      <section class="legal-section" id="scope">
        <h2>Scope</h2>
        <p>
          Inkcreate is a notebook capture and organization product that lets users create notebooks,
          chapters, pages, and date-based notepad pages, upload photos, store notes, run OCR-related
          workflows, and optionally connect a personal Google Drive account for exports or backups.
        </p>
        <p>
          This Privacy Policy applies to the public website, the signed-in workspace, the mobile-friendly
          web experience, and services that support uploads, background jobs, OCR, search, and Drive export.
          If a company, school, or other organization operates a hosted Inkcreate deployment for you,
          that operator may provide additional privacy disclosures that apply alongside this policy.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section" id="information-we-collect">
        <h2>Information we collect</h2>
        <ul class="legal-list">
          <li>
            <strong>Account and profile data.</strong> When you create an account, we collect information such as
            your email address, encrypted password credentials, role, locale, and time zone.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Notebook and page content.</strong> We collect the titles, notes, descriptions, dates,
            ordering metadata, and other content you create in notebooks, chapters, pages, and notepad pages.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Photos and attachments.</strong> We collect images and files you upload or capture through the app,
            including notebook page photos and any related metadata needed to store and display them.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Operational and usage data.</strong> We collect request identifiers, timestamps, IP-derived
            request data, browser and device context, session cookies, and time-zone data needed to keep the app
            secure, signed in, and correctly localized.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Google Drive connection data.</strong> If you connect Google Drive, we store the connection state,
            selected folder identifiers, and encrypted OAuth tokens needed to export or sync your content to your Drive account.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Generated and processed data.</strong> We may create OCR results, search indexes, export manifests,
            and background job records that help us process, search, and deliver your content.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section" id="how-we-use-information">
        <h2>How we use information</h2>
        <p>We use the information we collect to operate and improve Inkcreate, including to:</p>
        <ul class="legal-list">
          <li>authenticate users, maintain sessions, and secure accounts;</li>
          <li>store, organize, and display notebooks, pages, notes, and uploaded photos;</li>
          <li>run OCR, indexing, summaries, exports, and background processing workflows you request;</li>
          <li>apply your selected time zone, locale, and workspace settings;</li>
          <li>troubleshoot, monitor reliability, prevent abuse, and investigate security issues; and</li>
          <li>support backups and exports, including delivery to your connected Google Drive folder when enabled.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section" id="ocr-storage-drive">
        <h2>OCR, storage, and Google Drive</h2>
        <p>
          Inkcreate is designed around image capture and structured storage. Photos and files may be stored in the
          storage system configured for the deployment, including direct browser uploads to object storage. Notes,
          notebook structure, metadata, and related records are stored in the application database.
        </p>
        <p>
          When you trigger OCR, reprocessing, or other content workflows, your uploaded content may be processed by
          background workers and OCR-related services configured for the deployment. When you connect Google Drive,
          Inkcreate can copy your notes, manifests, and attached images into the Google Drive folder you choose.
          Content exported to your own Drive account is then also subject to Google’s terms, policies, sharing settings,
          and retention controls.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section" id="sharing">
        <h2>Sharing and disclosures</h2>
        <p>We do not sell your notebook content. We may disclose information in these situations:</p>
        <ul class="legal-list">
          <li>to service providers that host or process the app, storage, OCR jobs, background work, or email delivery;</li>
          <li>to Google when you authorize a Google Drive connection and request exports or backups;</li>
          <li>if required to comply with law, regulation, court order, or valid legal process;</li>
          <li>to investigate fraud, abuse, security incidents, or violations of our terms; or</li>
          <li>as part of a business transfer, merger, or asset sale, subject to applicable law.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section" id="retention">
        <h2>Retention and deletion</h2>
        <p>
          We retain account records and workspace content for as long as needed to provide the service, comply with legal
          obligations, resolve disputes, and protect the service. You can edit or delete content inside the app, and you can
          disconnect Google Drive at any time from Settings.
        </p>
        <p>
          Exported files that already exist in your Google Drive account are controlled by you and by Google Drive after export.
          Deleting content inside Inkcreate does not automatically remove copies already exported to your Drive unless the product
          explicitly says it will do so.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section" id="security">
        <h2>Security</h2>
        <p>
          We use administrative, technical, and organizational measures intended to protect your information, including access
          controls, authenticated sessions, request forgery protection, and encrypted storage for sensitive Google OAuth tokens.
          No method of transmission or storage is perfectly secure, so we cannot guarantee absolute security.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section" id="choices">
        <h2>Your choices</h2>
        <ul class="legal-list">
          <li>update your notebooks, pages, notes, profile, and time-zone settings inside the product;</li>
          <li>disconnect Google Drive or change the selected export folder in Settings;</li>
          <li>delete content you no longer want stored in the app; and</li>
          <li>use the operator contact details published for your Inkcreate deployment if you need help with account or privacy requests.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section" id="changes">
        <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect product changes, legal requirements, or operational needs.
          When we make material changes, we may update the effective date, publish the revised policy here, and provide additional
          notice where appropriate.
        </p>
      </section>
    </article>
  </main>

  <%= render "shared/public_auth_cta",
    eyebrow: "Try Inkcreate",
    title: "See how the signed-out flow leads into the workspace.",
    body: "Use the same mobile-friendly capture flow, then review notes, OCR text, and exports inside a single organized workspace." %>

  <%= render "shared/public_footer" %>
</div>
